<br>
In a multi-PC conflict, from a group to a raid--only the lead tank needs to know what to attack next.  Everyone else should key off of them.  If you need mana from the mobs, then make sure a caster is left.<br>
<br>
In most large fight situations, just let the lead tank move to the next hardest mob they see, and keep the rest asleep--don't bitch if he wakes up the one you most recently mezzed, at least they're assisting. <p><img src="http://www.discoverynet.com/~eugee/xornn.sig.jpg"><br>
