 When puller comes with more than one pull, let the main tank target and begin attack one mob (he should have a hotkey telling who is attacking). The enchanter/s in that moment should mesmerize all. If all are doing well, you will see one attacking mob, and the others mezzed. Then the wizzis should root each mezed-mob, and shamis may slow them down (also ensnare will help), but remember NOT TO DAMAGE IT. When the mob is dead, the enchanter should say who is next to kill (why the enchanter? cause he knows who will be hard to keep mezzed). Normal is kill the casters first, and after the warriors (at lvl 39 that changes, chanters have a manatap-over-time, and they gain mana when a caster mob mezzed)...<br>
 more: if the enchanter that tryes to mezz something is going to die, heal him! dont attack the mob, or dont try to nuke'em, or dont try to root'em (druid root, that does damage). If a chanter is taking serious hits and trying to mezz at the same time, if you attack the mob, the mob will still agro on the enchanter PLUS if the chanter finally mezz it, you will break mezz (and probably the chanter will die)... a good tactic is having a cleric/pally stuning the mob until the mezz works... you can also try bard charm, it will give those seconds to mezz the mob...<br>
 another thing: organization. There should be a raid-leader, who will tell all the moment what to do, who loots, and when to move. That will salve you from nasty roamer trains...<br>
